name: CardiacArrhythmias
title: Cardiac Arrhythmias
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining cardiac arrhythmia diagnoses, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad group of diagnosis concepts for cardiac arrhythmias of all types, including procedures done for treating arrhythmias such as cardiac pacemakers and ablations.),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the Disorder (Clinical finding) branch, though some can be in the Situation or the Procedure branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes cardiac arrhythmias of all types; cardiac conduction disorders; cardiac arrest; history of cardiac arrhythmias; or history of arrhythmia treatment with cardioversion, ablation, or other procedures specifically for arrhythmias.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes placement of cardiac defibrillators and their complications, since those may be placed for primary prevention in patients with systolic dysfunction at risk for ventricular arrhythmias but without any personal history of rhythm disorder.)
